JOHANNESBURG - National Police Commissioner Khehla Sitole says cash-in-transit robbers are constantly adjusting their tactics. At least 45 cash heists have been reported this year alone, with Gauteng recording the highest number. EXCLUSIVE: Police unit tasked to battle heists not qualified The robberies have also been increasingly violent. Sitole has reassured South Africans that police are working hard to deal effectively with cash-in-transit robberies.